brief_summary.textblock: To identify the bladder diary parameters that are best correlated to VSD.

clinical_study.brief_title: The Best Parameter of Bladder Diary Correlates With the Volume at Strong Desire to Void of Filling Cystometry

detailed_description.textblock: To identify the bladder diary parameters that are best correlated to VSD.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Female patients with lower urinary tract symptoms who had underwent urodynamic
             studies

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients without data of bladder diary

study_pop.textblock: Female patients with lower urinary tract symptoms

clinical_study.keyword: bladder capacity; bladder diary; bladder oversensitivity; lower urinary tract symptoms

facility.name: Department of Obstetrics & Gynecology, National Taiwan University Hospital

clinical_study.official_title: The Best Parameter of Bladder Diary Correlates With the Volume at Strong Desire to Void of Filling Cystometry

oversight_info.authority: Taiwan: Department of Health, Executive Yuan.

primary_outcome.description: To identify which bladder diary parameter that is best correlated to the volume at strong desire to void of filling cystometry. Thus, that bladder diary parameter may be used as a surrogate for the volume of strong desire to void of filling cystometry and without the need of urodynamic studies.
primary_outcome.measure: To identify the bladder diary parameter that is best correlated to the volume at strong desire to void of filling cystometry.
